zecs85&amp;w=3D640&amp;q=3D75"></div></div><div class=3D"Readme_readme__1Pr=
3p markdown-next" id=3D"readme"><p>A simple system-wide color picker. The c=
olor picker can be triggered with a standalone command or as part of the me=
nu bar command. The menu bar shows the last nine picked colors. The Organiz=
e Colors command can be used to see all colors.</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://github.com/LitoMore/raycast-cross-extension-conventio=
ns"><img src=3D"https://shields.io/badge/Raycast-Cross--Extension-eee?label=
Color=3DFF6363&amp;logo=3Draycast&amp;logoColor=3Dfff&amp;style=3Dflat-squa=
re" alt=3D"raycast-cross-extension-badge"></a></p>
<h2>Key Features</h2>
<ul>
<li>Pick a color on your desktop</li>
<li>Access your colors from the menu bar</li>
<li>Organize your colors</li>
<li>Generate colors using UI</li>
<li>Pick a color using AI</li>
<li>Pick a color with color wheel</li>
<li>Convert any color to a different format</li>
<li>Get the color name for a hex code</li>
</ul>
<h2>API</h2>
<p>This extensions follows <a href=3D"https://github.com/LitoMore/raycast-c=
ross-extension-conventions">Raycast Cross-Extension Conventions</a>.</p>
<p>You can use <code>crossLaunchCommand</code> to use the picker color resu=
lt.</p>
<h3>Launch Context Options</h3>
<h4><code>copyToClipboard</code></h4>
<p>Type: <code>boolean</code><br>
Default: <code>false</code></p>
<p>Copy to clipboard is disabled by default. Set it to <code>true</code> to=
 enable copy action.</p>
<h4><code>callbackLaunchOptions</code></h4>
<p>Type: <code>LaunchOptions</code><br>
Default: <code>undefined</code></p>
<p>Use this option to let this extension know what kind of callback needs t=
o be performed when <code>crossLaunchCommand</code>.</p>
<h3>Callback Context Options</h3>
<h4><code>hex</code></h4>
<p>Type: <code>string</code></p>
<p>It returns the color picker hex result.</p>
<h4><code>formattedColor</code></h4>
<p>Type: <code>string</code></p>
<p>It returns the formatted color result. The format can be changed in the =
preferences of the extension.</p>
<h3>Examples</h3>
<h4>Launch Color Picker</h4>
<pre><code class=3D"language-typescript"><span>import</span> { <span>Launch=
Type</span> } <span>from</span> <span>"@raycast/api"</span>;
<span>import</span> { crossLaunchCommand } <span>from</span> <span>"raycast=
-cross-extension"</span>;

<span>await</span> <span>crossLaunchCommand</span>({
  <span>name</span>: <span>"pick-color"</span>,
  <span>type</span>: <span>LaunchType</span>.<span>UserInitiated</span>,
  <span>extensionName</span>: <span>"color-picker"</span>,
  <span>ownerOrAuthorName</span>: <span>"thomas"</span>,
});
</code></pre>
<h4>Launch Color Wheel</h4>
<pre><code class=3D"language-typescript"><span>import</span> { <span>Launch=
Type</span> } <span>from</span> <span>"@raycast/api"</span>;
<span>import</span> { crossLaunchCommand } <span>from</span> <span>"raycast=
-cross-extension"</span>;

<span>await</span> <span>crossLaunchCommand</span>({
  <span>name</span>: <span>"color-wheel"</span>,
  <span>type</span>: <span>LaunchType</span>.<span>UserInitiated</span>,
  <span>extensionName</span>: <span>"color-picker"</span>,
  <span>ownerOrAuthorName</span>: <span>"thomas"</span>,
});
</code></pre>
<h4>Rececive Callback Result</h4>
<pre><code class=3D"language-typescript"><span>import</span> { <span>Launch=
Props</span> } <span>from</span> <span>"@raycast/api"</span>;

<span>type</span> <span>LaunchContext</span> =3D {
  hex?: <span>string</span>;
};

<span>export</span> <span>default</span> <span>function</span> <span>Comman=
d</span>(<span>{ launchContext =3D {} }: LaunchProps&lt;{ launchContext?: L=
aunchContext }&gt;</span>) {
  <span>useEffect</span>(<span>() =3D&gt;</span> {
    <span>if</span> (launchContext.<span>hex</span>) {
      <span>console</span>.<span>log</span>(launchContext.<span>hex</span>)=
;
    }
  }, []);
}
</code></pre>
<h2>Who's using Color Picker Cross-Extension API</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://raycast.com/litomore/badges">Badges - shields.io</a>=
 - Concise, consistent, and legible badges</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Perfect for Web Development and Beyond</strong></h2>
<p>Whether you're tweaking CSS, fine-tuning gradients, or selecting the per=
fect hue for your next design project, Color Picker is your go-to tool. Fro=
m HEX to RGB, HSL to CMYK, we've got all your color values covered.</p>
<h2><strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong></h2>
<h3><strong>How do I activate Color Picker?</strong></h3>
<p>Launching the Color Picker is easy. Simply hit your Raycast hotkey (defa=
ult is =E2=8C=98+Space) and type "color picker" or "pick color". The extens=
ion will spring to life, ready to capture any hue on your screen. If you're=
 looking to integrate it with your extension you can trigger the color pick=
er programmatically using the <code>crossLaunchCommand</code> function.</p>
<h3><strong>What is the command for Color Picker?</strong></h3>
<p>Raycast's Color Picker doesn't rely on complex commands - it's all about=
 simplicity and speed. The primary commands are:</p>
<ol>
<li><code>pick-color</code>: This launches the main color picker interface.=
</li>
<li><code>color-wheel</code>: Opens the interactive color wheel for precise=
 hue selection.</li>
<li><code>organize-colors</code>: Allows you to manage and categorize your =
color palettes.</li>
</ol>
<p>Pro tip: These commands can be customized or aliased in your Raycast pre=
ferences for even quicker access.</p>
<h3><strong>How does the Color Picker tool work?</strong></h3>
<p>Raycast's Color Picker tool is a powerhouse of functionality. Here's a b=
reakdown of its core operations:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Screen Sampling</strong>: Click anywhere on your screen to inst=
antly capture the color of any pixel.</li>
<li><strong>Format Flexibility</strong>: The picked color is immediately av=
ailable in multiple formats - HEX, RGB, HSL, and CMYK. Convert between thes=
e with a single click.</li>
<li><strong>Color Wheel</strong>: Fine-tune your selection using the intera=
ctive color wheel, adjusting hue, saturation, and brightness.</li>
<li><strong>AI Integration</strong>: Leverage machine learning to generate =
complementary colors or entire palettes based on your picked color.</li>
<li><strong>Cross-App Compatibility</strong>: Thanks to our API, the Color =
Picker can seamlessly interact with other Raycast extensions.</li>
<li><strong>Clipboard Integration</strong>: Copy picked colors directly to =
your clipboard for instant use in design apps or code editors.</li>
</ol></div></div><div class=3D"ExtensionPage_side__FsYLh"><div class=3D"Sid=
